ARBITRAL AWARD

IN THE ARBITRAL PROCEEDINGS
UNDER THE ARBITRATION AND CONCILIATION ACT, 1996

CLAIMANT: M/s. Rajputana Builders Pvt. Ltd., Udaipur
RESPONDENT: Rajasthan Medical Services Corporation Ltd. (RMSCL), Jaipur
SOLE ARBITRATOR: Justice (Retd.) R.K. Vyas (Former Judge, Rajasthan High Court)
DATE OF AWARD: 15.11.2026

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
FINDINGS OF THE ARBITRATOR
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Issue 1: Whether RMSCL is liable for site handover delay?
FINDING: YES. The Site Possession Certificate itself records the actual date of possession as 20.05.2024.
RMSCL's failure to demolish the existing structure caused the delay. Claim No. 1 ALLOWED in full.

Issue 2: Whether Variation Orders are payable?
FINDING: YES. 9 out of 11 Variation Orders are supported by Engineer's written instructions.
2 VOs requiring verification — amounts reduced. Claim No. 2 ALLOWED ₹5.40 Crore (reduced from ₹6.15 Cr).

Issue 3: Price Escalation under Clause 10CC?
FINDING: ALLOWED in full. WPI indices and methodology correctly applied.
Claim No. 3 ALLOWED ₹3.94 Crore.

Issue 4: Idle Labour & Machinery?
FINDING: PARTLY ALLOWED — Drawing delay by RMSCL for 60 days proven (not 90 days).
Claim No. 4 ALLOWED ₹1.45 Crore (reduced).

Issue 5: Loss of Profit?
FINDING: PARTLY ALLOWED — Wrongful termination established. Hudson Formula applicable.
Claim No. 5 ALLOWED ₹2.49 Crore.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
COUNTER CLAIM FINDINGS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

CC-1: Re-tendering cost — REJECTED (Termination itself was wrongful)
CC-2: Liquidated Damages — REJECTED (Delay was primarily Employer's fault — O.P. Bhasin v. HSIDC followed)
CC-3: Supervision cost — REJECTED

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
AWARD
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The Claimant is hereby awarded:
- Claim No. 1:  ₹4.82 Crore
- Claim No. 2:  ₹5.40 Crore
- Claim No. 3:  ₹3.94 Crore
- Claim No. 4:  ₹1.45 Crore
- Claim No. 5:  ₹2.49 Crore
TOTAL:          ₹18.10 Crore

With interest @ 9% per annum from 15.01.2026 till date of realization.
Security Deposit and Performance Guarantee to be RELEASED immediately.
EOT of 8 months GRANTED.
Termination declared ILLEGAL and VOID.
Cost of arbitration (₹8,50,000) to be borne by RMSCL.

Sd/-
Justice (Retd.) R.K. Vyas
Sole Arbitrator
Date: 15.11.2026
Place: Udaipur
